{
  "texts": [
    "Given the rapid growth in the use of LLMs (Porter, 2023) and that, at the time of writing, LLM usage was highest among people aged 34 and under (Similar Web, 2023), the tests we examined are used primarily as remote, unproctored tests for screening recent college graduates (Similar Web, 2023).",
    "Backed by research suggesting that unproctored pre-employment testing does not lead to substantially inflated scores or decreases in criterion-related validity (e.g., Beaty et al., 2011; Lievens & Burke, 2011), many employers now routinely assess candidates remotely.",
    "However, if LLMs score well on validated cognitive ability tests designed for personnel selection, our field may need to reassess concerns about unproctored testing.",
    "Our investigation provides three major contributions.",
    "First, we compare LLM performance on two common types of cognitive tests: quantitative ability and verbal ability."
  ]
}